<tr><td align="left" valign="bottom" width="98%"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/toptab.gif" width="98" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td><td align="left" valign="bottom" width="22">&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Light Side Retrieval Engines and Perhaps the Most Broken Card in the Game   <br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=19577'>Jonathan "Fluke Skywalker" Swindells</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=19577&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> September 18, 2008</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> I was reading the rulebook the other day and came across what was, for me, quite a shocking revelation. More on that later, but it prompted me to look at light side retrieval options in a bit more detail than I ever have before. This is what I found.<br />
<br />
As the light player there are 7 objectives and a further 96 cards that allow you to retrieve force. Some of these are very popular, while others are almost never included (in both cases, for good reasons). All are listed (but only once) somewhere in this article along with the portion of their game text that deals with retrieval Unless stated, retrieval is permitted at least once per turn for each card.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
1. If were talking about a retrieval engine then this has to be something that functions turn after turn. If my car engine stopped half way to where I was going Id not be very happy and a retrieval engine that stops part way through the game is likewise useless. For this reason Im going to eliminate the following cards, which either place stuff out of play or are only usable a limited number of times per game (either specifically limited by their game text or just because recycling the cards required is likely to prove unfeasible and the retrieval will therefore be unsustainable).<br />
<br />
Out of play:<br />
Heroic Sacrifice  Retrieve 2 for each Heroic Sacrifice on table by placing a just-forfeited rebel of ability >2 out of play<br />
*Let&#39;s Keep A Little Optimism Here  May place out of play to retrieve 1 force<br />
Noble Sacrifice  Place out of play a character with the same power as one the opponent just deployed to retrieve force equal to your characters forfeit<br />
*Wokling (V)  Retrieve 1 by placing out of play<br />
<br />
Once per game:<br />
*All Wings Report In  Once per game retrieve X (= number of copies of a particular non-unique starfighter on table) by drawing destiny <X<br />
Boonta Eve Podrace  Retrieve 6 for winning the pod race<br />
*Might Of The Republic  Once per game, retrieve 1 for each senator at senate<br />
Mind What You Have Learned/Save You It Can  Retrieve 10 by flipping (if Yoda (V) not on table)<br />
*Nar Shaddaa Wind Chimes  Once per game retrieve X (= number of copies of a particular non-unique character on table) by drawing destiny <X<br />
*Nar Shaddaa Wind Chimes & *Out Of Somewhere  Once per game retrieve X (= number of copies of a particular non-unique character on table) by drawing destiny <X<br />
*See-Threepio  Once per game, retrieve 3 by replacing another C-3PO<br />
*The Shield Is Down!  When Bunker blown away retrieve 8 force<br />
You Can Either Profit By This.../Or Be Destroyed  Once per game retrieve 5 (10 if Hans power <4) by flipping<br />
<br />
Probably unsustainable:<br />
*Cloud City: Casino  Retrieve 2 whenever your gambler present wins Cloud City Sabacc (3 if Lando)<br />
*Corporal Marmor  Retrieve 1 by deploying a starfighter to same docking bay<br />
*Gold 3  Retrieve 1 by deploying to Dantooine<br />
*Gold 4  Retrieve 1 by deploying to Anoat<br />
*Gold 6  Retrieve 1 by deploying to Kashyyyk<br />
*Graxol Kelvyyn  Retrieve 1 if winning the podrace (lose 1 if losing the podrace)<br />
*Great Shot, Kid!  Retrieve 3 by deploying a unique starship to a system if Death Star blown away<br />
*Jess  Retrieve 1 whenever you deploy a musician to same site<br />
Local Uprising/Liberation  (7 side) Retrieve 1 when you deploy a matching operative to the subjugated planet<br />
*Strikeforce (V)  Place in lost pile to retrieve a starship<br />
*Yerka Mig (V)  Retrieve 1 whenever you deploy a unique alien to a battleground<br />
*Yoda (V)  Retrieve 3 each time you complete a Jedi Test<br />
<br />
If you have any serious objection to this list, please consider that Im not saying theres no way youll be able to recycle the use of these necessarily, only that it would be a fools errand to try because doing so would likely use up too many card slots to leave room for any reasonable damage-causing strategy.<br />
<br />
Cloud City: Casino is included because of the defensive shield that allows cancelling of Sabacc. For the rest I am basically assuming that you will run out of cards of the right sort to deploy eventually (although I appreciate this may not be true with Great Shot, Kid! if your opponent allows you to deploy your starship from lost pile, battle them in space, and forfeit the starship again as this will give you a net retrieval of 2 for the turn).<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
2. The cards and events involved have to be under your control, so those that retrieve based on some action that depends almost entirely on your opponent also need to be discounted. These are as follows:<br />
<br />
Characters:<br />
***Gran  Retrieve 1 whenever opponent initiates battle at same/adjacent site<br />
*Lando Calrissian, Scoundrel  Retrieve 1 when opponent initiates battle at same location<br />
*Laudica (V)  Retrieve 1 whenever opponent force drains at a non-battleground<br />
*Princess Leia Organa  Retrieve 5 if released<br />
*Princess Leia Organa (V)  Retrieve 3 if released<br />
Snivvian  Retrieve 2 when opponent cancels Nightfall at related system<br />
*Tauntaun Bones  Retrieve 1 if opponent draws destiny 4<br />
Defensive Shields:<br />
Weapons Display (V)  Retrieve 1 if you occupy a battleground site & system and opponent deploys a card with ability but does not battle<br />
Effects:<br />
*A Tremor In The Force (V)  Retrieve 1 whenever you verify opponents reserve deck<br />
*Slayn & Korpil Facilities  Retrieve 2 whenever your starfighter or vehicle hits an opponents starship or vehicle<br />
*The Planet That It&#39;s Farthest From (V)  Retrieve X (= opponents force drain bonuses) whenever opponent force drains but you control more battlegrounds<br />
Immediate Effects:<br />
Heroic Sacrifice (V)  Retrieve 1 by deploying on an opponents just-deployed maintenance card<br />
Interrupts:<br />
*Either Way, You Win  You retrieve 3 & opponent retrieves 1, or you activate 4 & opponent activates 2 (opponents choice)<br />
Locations:<br />
*Death Star: Detention Block Corridor  Retrieve 1 whenever you release a captive here (4 if Leia)<br />
Objectives:<br />
We&#39;ll Handle This/Duel Of The Fates  Retrieve 1 by flipping back to 0 side<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
3. There are some decks where you will not be able to initiate battles yourself due to your opponents strategy. Cards that allow retrieval that is conditional on you initiating battles are:<br />
<br />
Characters:<br />
*Tawss Khaa  Retrieve 1 by predicting the winner in a battle you just initiated where he is present<br />
Effects:<br />
*Civil Disorder (V)  Retrieve top character in lost pile (with no maintenance cost or permanent weapon) by initiating battle<br />
*Draw Their Fire  Retrieve 1 for initiating battle (opponent also loses 1)<br />
Interrupts:<br />
*Our Only Hope (V)  If Luke just won a battle or duel, retrieve any 1 card<br />
Objectives:<br />
The Hyperdrive Generator&#39;s Gone/We&#39;ll Need A New One  (7 side) Retrieve 1 whenever you draw battle destiny<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
4. Now for what I appreciated for the first time this week, and the real point of this article. So what do I think is the most broken card in the game at present? Perhaps surprisingly in an article about light side retrieval Id like to put forward the case for the dark side defensive shield Do They Have A Code Clearance? which allows the dark player to grab their opponents interrupts and utinni effects (once completed), stack them on the defensive shield, and reduce their opponents future retrieval by the number of cards stacked.<br />
<br />
There are several things about this card. Its status as a defensive shield means that the dark side can (and in my opinion, should) always have it on table from the start of the game onwards, and it cant be cancelled, suspended or anything else. Secondly, you dont have to use any force to operate its game text, just grab your opponents interrupt or utinni effect with glee. So effectively youve got a grabber that can remove any unwanted retrieval interrupts from the light side.<br />
<br />
But thats not even the best bit, because the real sting with this card is that last bit of text. Opponents force retrieval is reduced by X where X = the number of cards here. What hadnt occurred to me before was that by getting a card here the light player can no longer use anything that retrieves only 1 card, since it will be reduced to zero. This includes all the Back interrupts that Plastoid Armor (V) was so good for pulling, but also other key things like Luke Skywalker (V), Baragwins and many others.<br />
<br />
The warning that comes with this is therefore that you have to be extremely careful about when you choose to use an interrupt or utinni effect to retrieve force, because it may well be the last time you are able to retrieve anything for that game.<br />
<br />
Your only way round this (as far as I am aware) is to have the Outrider on table, as this places utinni effects that retrieve out of play once completed (which will be a mandatory action that occurs before your opponent has chance to grab the utinni effect). However, this gives these cards the disadvantages that I outlined in section 1.<br />
<br />
Interrupts and utinni effects that retrieve (not already listed in previous sections) are:<br />
<br />
Interrupts:<br />
Advance Preparation  Use 3 to retrieve Attack Run<br />
Advance Preparation (V)  Retrieve 1 force (or any 1 card if One In A Million on table)<br />
*Ambush (V)  Use 2 to retrieve any one card into hand if your clones occupy 3 related battlegrounds<br />
*Artoo, Come Back At Once!  Use 1 to retrieve R2-D2<br />
Effective Repairs  Use 3 to retrieve an effect of any kind into hand<br />
*Endor Celebration (V)  Retrieve 5 if you have a rebel scout alone at Back Door<br />
Found Someone You Have (V)  Retrieve top character of lost pile into hand<br />
Han&#39;s Back  Use 1 to retrieve Han<br />
Han&#39;s Back (V)  Use 1 to retrieve Han, Falcon or Hans Heavy Blaster Pistol<br />
*Harvest If Owen or Beru on table, retrieve any 1 card (2 if both on table, 4 if both at Lars Moisture Farm)<br />
Jedi Levitation (V)  Use 3 to retrieve a non-maintenance character into hand<br />
Leia&#39;s Back  Use 1 to retrieve Leia<br />
Leia&#39;s Back (V)  Use 1 to retrieve Leia, Leias Blaster Rifle or Leias Sporting Blaster<br />
Luke&#39;s Back  Use 1 to retrieve Luke<br />
Luke&#39;s Back (V)  Use 1 to retrieve non-Jedi Luke, Lukes Blaster Pistol or Lukes Lightsaber<br />
*Neck And Neck  If both players have <10 force remaining, both retrieve 4 force<br />
*Off The Edge  Retrieve X (= difference between your destiny and destiny number of your character at a Cloud City site)<br />
On The Edge  Retrieve X (= any number from 1 to 6, chosen by you) by drawing destiny >X<br />
Rebel Reinforcements  Use 1 to retrieve X (= a destiny draw) rebel troopers and/or Y-wings<br />
Rebel Reinforcements (V)  Use 1 to retrieve X (= a destiny draw) rebels and/or rebel starships<br />
Return Of A Jedi  Use 1 to retrieve Obi-Wan<br />
Return Of A Jedi (V)  Use 1 to retrieve Obi-Wan, Obi-Wans Cape or Obi-Wans Lightsaber<br />
*Skull (V)  Use 3 to retrieve a creature<br />
Starship Levitation (V)  Use 3 to retrieve a non-maintenance starship into hand<br />
Thank The Maker  Use 1 to retrieve X (= a destiny draw) after opponent force drains for >5 if you have a droid on table. The drain only needs to be >3 if you have Hopping Mad (V) on table. <br />
Were You Looking For Me?  Retrieve C-3PO<br />
*Yoda, You Seek Yoda  Use 1 to retrieve Yoda<br />
*Yub Yub!  Retrieve 1 card with Ewok in title<br />
<br />
Utinni Effects:<br />
*Death Star Plans  Draw 3 destiny and retrieve that much force by having a droid steal the plans and take them to Yavin 4<br />
*Kessel Run  Retrieve X (= parsec difference between Kessel and another system) by travelling between them & back again<br />
*Our Most Desperate Hour  Move a rebel from Tatooine to Alderaan to retrieve force based on the number of characters you have on table who are force-attuned, force-sensitive or Jedi<br />
*Rycar&#39;s Run  Retrieve X (= twice the number of asteroid sectors at a system) by travelling between the system and related Big One & back again<br />
*The First Transport Is Away!  Retrieve X (= twice the number of passengers) by moving a medium transport from a Hoth site to target (non-Hoth) system<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
5. Retrieval is, of course, particularly important when youre getting low on resources and struggling to get things on table and keep them there. While a good retrieval engine may help prevent you from ending up in this situation, you wont necessarily be able to rely on cards that require you to hold specific locations late in the game. These include:<br />
<br />
*Cloud City Celebration  Retrieve 1 for each Cloud City battleground site you occupy (cancelled if opponent controls the system)<br />
*Coruscant Celebration  Retrieve 1 for each Coruscant battleground site you occupy (cancelled if opponent controls the system)<br />
*Frostbite (V)  Retrieve 1 for each Hoth site you control with a unique combat vehicle<br />
*Tatooine Celebration  Retrieve 1 for each Tatooine battleground site you occupy (cancelled if opponent controls the system)<br />
*Tatooine: Marketplace  Use 2 to retrieve 1 if you control the site<br />
*They Win This Round  Retrieve 4 by taking over a site opponent controls<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
6. Many cards are limited to only retrieving specific card types, which means that you will need a variety of these in your deck to permit retrieval of several different card types, or a way of swapping cards into your lost pile from hand, such as Baragwin, or Bionic Hand (V). Im slightly disappointed to have to put the Baragwin in here actually because I do think theyre really quite useful, but objectively the cap fits so hell have to wear it.<br />
<br />
Agents In The Court/No Love For The Empire  (7 side) Retrieve a non-unique alien or reps species<br />
*Attark (V)  Retrieve a non-unique alien of a species different to your rep if No Love For The Empire on table<br />
***Baragwin  Use 1 to retrieve top card of lost pile if it is a weapon, device or transport vehicle<br />
*Cloud City: Downtown Plaza  Use 1 to retrieve a Cloud City location<br />
*Cloud City: Incinerator  Use 3 to retrieve a droid if you occupy<br />
*Jek Porkins (V)  Use 1 to retrieve a Rogue squadron pilot or X-wing if piloting Red 6<br />
*Koensayr Manufacturing  Retrieve a Y-wing (deploys on Ralltiir; suspended while opponent controls Ralltiir)<br />
Rebel Strike Team/Garrison Destroyed  (7 side) Retrieve a rebel scout of ability <3<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
7. The remainder of the cards are probably the easiest to use for force retrieval. Some will clearly work together, but may while others are incompatible. For example, Bail Organa is not compatible with Episode 1 senate cards.<br />
<br />
Episode 1 Senate:<br />
*Queen Amidala, Ruler Of Naboo  Retrieve 1 for each Naboo site you control, while she is in a senate majority<br />
*Yarua  Retrieve 1 whenever you force drain at a battleground system, while he is in a senate majority<br />
<br />
Original Trilogy Senate:<br />
 *Bail Organa  Retrieve 1 if opponent loses force to a drain caused by a rebel, while at senate<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
8. So that whittles the list down to a very select few that I havent excluded. This can still be divided into the popular and the not so popular. To deal with the unpopular ones first:<br />
<br />
***Droid Merchant  Retrieve 1 whenever you deploy an astromech to a starfighter (cumulative)<br />
[Initially I had put this in section 1 under the probably unsustainable section but actually, in combination with Spaceport Speeders and sending the droid to the used pile this may be quite a reasonable method as it could be done at, for example, a shielded Echo Docking Bay.]<br />
<br />
*I Did It!  If youve won a podrace, retrieve 4 by placing Boonta Eve Podrace out of play (once per game) & place bottom card of lost pile on top of force pile once per control phase if you occupy a battleground site & system<br />
[Still requires presence on both land and in space. Would have gone under section 5 if it wasnt for the fact that these can be any site & system, rather than specific ones.]<br />
<br />
*Reflection  Use 3 to retrieve 1<br />
[Simply too expensive in my opinion: using 4 force to retrieve 1 by the time you add on the one from Secret Plans isnt practical]<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
9. That leaves the cards I can find no good reason to exclude:<br />
<br />
*Figrin D&#39;an  Use 1 to make wager (you draw 3 destiny, opponent draws 2). Higher total retrieves 1<br />
*Flash Of Insight (V)  Placed in used pile during draw phase. You may retrieve 1 at the same time.<br />
*Luke Skywalker (V)  Retrieve 1 if piloting at a battleground<br />
*Uh-oh! (V)  Retrieve 1 for each battleground site you control with a musician<br />
<br />
Of course these all have their drawbacks too, but if they didnt theyd be broken wouldnt they?<br />
